  "response": "Rahul Gandhi is an Indian politician and a prominent member of the Indian National Congress party. He comes from a lineage deeply rooted in Indian politics, being the son of former Prime Minister Rajiv Gandhi and Sonia Gandhi, and the grandson of Indira Gandhi and Jawaharlal Nehru, both of whom also served as Prime Ministers of India.\n\nHe entered politics in 2004, winning the Lok Sabha seat from Amethi, a constituency previously held by his father and mother. He served as the President of the Indian National Congress from 2017 to 2019.\n\nThroughout his political career, Rahul Gandhi has been a vocal critic of economic inequality and has advocated for policies aimed at empowering farmers, laborers, and marginalized communities. He has often emphasized the need for inclusive growth and social justice.",
